            "type": "section", 
            "subtype": "special_abilities", 
            "sections": [
                {
                    "body": "A cannon golem's slam and cannon attacks count as adamantine, cold iron, and silver for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.", 
                    "name": "Alloyed", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 3/Monsters/Golem/Cannon/Golem/Cannon/Special Abilities/Alloyed", 
                    "ability_types": {
                        "ability_type": "Extraordinary"
                    }, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "When a cannon golem confirms a critical hit with a slam attack, it can make one cannon attack against that target as a free action (as long as the cannon is loaded).", 
                    "name": "Blasting Critical", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 3/Monsters/Golem/Cannon/Golem/Cannon/Special Abilities/Blasting Critical", 
                    "ability_types": {
                        "ability_type": "Extraordinary"
                    }, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "The golem's cannon has a range increment of 100 feet and deals 6d6 points of bludgeoning and piercing damage on a hit with a &times;4 critical modifier. The cannon's magazine can hold up to 20 cannonballs at a time&mdash;reloading a single cannonball into this magazine is a standard action for the golem, while loading a cannonball into the cannon itself to fire it is a swift action; this allows the golem to take two shots per round with the cannon.", 
                    "name": "Cannon", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 3/Monsters/Golem/Cannon/Golem/Cannon/Special Abilities/Cannon", 
                    "ability_types": {
                        "ability_type": "Extraordinary"
                    }, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "A cannon golem adds its Dex modifier to the damage dealt by its cannon.", 
                    "name": "Gun Training", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 3/Monsters/Golem/Cannon/Golem/Cannon/Special Abilities/Gun Training", 
                    "ability_types": {
                        "ability_type": "Extraordinary"
                    }, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }, 
                {
                    "body": "A cannon golem is immune to spells and spell-like abilities that allow spell resistance. Certain spells and effects function differently against it, as noted below.", 
                    "name": "Immunity to Magic", 
                    "url": "pfsrd://Bestiary 3/Monsters/Golem/Cannon/Golem/Cannon/Special Abilities/Immunity to Magic", 
                    "sections": [
                        {
                            "body": "<ul class=\"stat-block-2\"><li>Any spell with the water descriptor that affects a cannon golem renders its cannon unusable for 1 round (no save).</li><li>A <i>heat metal</i> spell causes the golem's cannon to instantly backfire, dealing 6d6 points of damage to the golem and staggering it for 1 round (no save).</li></ul>", 
                            "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                            "type": "section"
                        }
                    ], 
                    "ability_types": {
                        "ability_type": "Extraordinary"
                    }, 
                    "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                    "type": "ability"
                }
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "body": "<p>A cannon golem's internal workings are a mechanical labyrinth; its extradimensional pockets constantly process new black powder. A cannon golem stands 12 feet tall.</p>", 
